    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>Walk the Catwalk</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20090423.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, April 23, 2009</b> &mdash;
    Millsberry fashionistas: prepare &mdash; or beware &mdash; because temptation is here! Loretta Rivers has let her spring fashion line loose. That&#039;s right, the <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">Wearhouse</a> boutique has been restocked with all-new spring items, ready to take you from the school playground to weekend fun, and back again. <br><br>The <i><i>Gazette</i></i> headed over to the store for a sneak peek, only to find ourselves surrounded by a spread of fake palm trees and sand. We sat down with Loretta for a quick Q & A:<br><br><i>Gazette</i>: &quot;Loretta! What is all this? Aren&#039;t you showcasing <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">new clothing</a>?&quot;<br><br>Loretta: &quot;Well, this year we&#039;re going to introduce the new line by throwing a fashion show! We&#039;re actually building a runway right now and, as you can see, the store&#039;s interior is based on the hot safari theme that&#039;s so popular this season!&quot;<br>
<br>
<i>Gazette</i>: &quot;Wow. It must be quite a line. Care to share a bit about what we should expect?&quot;<br><br>Loretta: &quot;Well, it&#039;s a &#039;<i>mixed bag</i>.&#039; We&#039;ve got everything from safari-style jackets to golf-inspired plaid pants. <br><br><i>Gazette</i>: &quot;And what would some of those light-hearted pieces include?&quot;<br><br>Loretta: &quot;Well, we have a nice watercolor-print dress that&#039;s almost sold out!&quot;<br><br><i>Gazette</i>: &quot;Do you create the designs yourself?&quot;<br><br>Loretta: &quot;No. But I did design these!&quot; (She kicks up her feet to show off a pair of yellow rain boots with red umbrellas dancing all over them.) <br><br><i>Gazette</i>: &quot;Hopefully those aren&#039;t on back order. We could <i>all</i> use a cute pair of rain boots for those April showers! So, what&#039;s hot this season in men&#039;s fashion?&quot;<br><br>Loretta: &quot;Men&#039;s fashion is a lot of fun this year. When it comes to color, anything goes. I told you about those plaid golf pants &mdash; well, those are for guys! (Laughs.) I&#039;d tell you more, but I need to leave a <i>little</i> mystery for the shoppers.&quot;<br><br><i>Gazette</i>: &quot;And who&#039;ll be modeling in the show?&quot;<br><br>Loretta: &quot;I&#039;ll only reveal two of them, for the time being. The first is reigning snowboard champion Kelly Kimbell. Now that winter is over, she&#039;s back and ready to go. And then there&#039;s Coach Danner. He volunteered because, believe it or not, he used to be a runway model!&quot;<br><br><i>Gazette</i>: &quot;Well, he definitely has the height for it! Wow &mdash; you learn something new every day, huh? So, one more question: do you need an extra model?&quot;<br><br>Loretta: &quot;Ha! Well &mdash; how do you feel about showing off some tie-dye?&quot;<br><br><i>Gazette</i>: &quot;Only if it comes with a guaranteed spot in one of those an open-air safari jeeps! <br><br>Loretta: (laughs) &quot;Well?&quot;<br><br>Interview concluded, the <i>Gazette</i> headed out. However, we couldn&#039;t help but notice different citizens &mdash; all balancing books on their heads! Runway-model practice, perhaps? There is always something brewing in Millsberry, so be sure to check out the new spring items at the Wearhouse. It&#039;s sure to add a little zing &mdash; or <i>bling</i> &mdash; to your spring!<br>
    </div>

